South African Wheat Prices Increase by the Daily Limit on Futures Exchange

-- B y   M k h u l u l i   M a n c o t y w a
-- 
2011-04-26T07:12:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/south-african-wheat-prices-increase-by-the-daily-limit-on-futures-exchange.html
South African wheat prices rose by
the daily limit of 100 rand in opening trading in Johannesburg.  Wheat for delivery in July, the most-active contract on the
South African futures exchange, rose by as much as 3.2 percent
to 3,274 rand a metric ton, and was trading 2.2 percent higher
at 3,245 rand as of 9:11 a.m. local time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mkhululi Mancotywa in Johannesburg at 
 mmancotywa1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  